{{define "quickstart"}}🚀 **Quickstart**

Create and bind an Octo bot for every one of your OpenClaw Agents in one shot, so each Agent can send and receive messages through Octo.

📋 **Send the following to OpenClaw to run (run /install first if the plugin isn't installed):**

```
Batch-create and bind Octo bots for all agents:
npx -y create-openclaw-octo quickstart --api-key {{.APIKey}} --api-url {{.APIURL}}
```{{end}}

{{define "install"}}📦 **Install / update the Octo plugin**

💡 We recommend upgrading OpenClaw to the latest version first for the best experience.

📋 **Send the following command to OpenClaw to run:**

```
npx -y create-openclaw-octo install
```

Once installed, use /newbot to create a single bot or /quickstart to batch-create.{{end}}

{{define "help"}}BotFather helps you create and manage bots.

**Available commands:**

- /install — install / update the Octo plugin
- /quickstart — AI Agent quickstart (recommended)
- /newbot — create a new bot
- /mybots — view my bots
- /connect — get the connection prompt
- /disconnect — disconnect an Agent
- /setname — change a bot's name
- /setdescription — change a bot's description
- /deletebot — delete a bot
- /token — view a token
- /revoke — reset a token
- /pending — view pending friend requests
- /approve — approve a friend request
- /reject — reject a friend request
- /cancel — cancel the current operation
- /help — show help{{end}}

{{define "connect_prompt"}}📋 Connection info for bot "**{{.DisplayName}}**":

**Bot Name:** {{.DisplayName}}  
**Bot ID:** {{.RobotID}}  
**Bot Token:** {{.BotToken}}  
**API Server:** {{.APIURL}}

📋 **Send the following to OpenClaw to run — it binds to the current Session's Agent by default (run /install to install the plugin first):**

```
Bind Octo bot {{.RobotID}} to an Agent.
By default it binds to the current Session's Agent; check the agent id with /status.
If the user specifies another Agent, replace it with the user-specified id.

npx -y create-openclaw-octo bind --bot-token {{.BotToken}} --api-url {{.APIURL}} --account-id {{.RobotID}} --agent <agent-id>
```

💡 **To bind to a different Agent, just change the `--agent` argument.**
🔌 To disconnect, send /disconnect{{end}}

{{define "created_prompt"}}✅ Bot "**{{.Name}}**" created!

**Bot Name:** {{.Name}}  
**Bot ID:** {{.RobotID}}  
**Bot Token:** {{.BotToken}}  
**API Server:** {{.APIURL}}

📋 **Send the following to OpenClaw to run — it binds to the current Session's Agent by default (run /install first if the plugin isn't installed):**

```
Bind Octo bot {{.RobotID}} to an Agent.
By default it binds to the current Session's Agent; check the agent id with /status.
If the user specifies another Agent, replace it with the user-specified id.

npx -y create-openclaw-octo bind --bot-token {{.BotToken}} --api-url {{.APIURL}} --account-id {{.RobotID}} --agent <agent-id>
```

💡 **To bind to a different Agent, just change the `--agent` argument.**{{end}}
